hat in Gods o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">dinar<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> way of worki<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">, <NOTE N="(i)" PLACE="marg">Rom 10 17 1 Cor 1 2. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"></NOTE> this Faith i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ought and beg<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> in men <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> of Ch<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ist <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span">
<PB N="7" REF="000635_0008_0FA9634993B32AC8" MS="y">
that be wanting, by the Testimony of the holy Scriptu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">es, in reading or hear|ing them read.</P>
<P>That <NOTE N="(k)" PLACE="marg">Gal 32 14 22 <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">3. Col 1 6 27 Ephes 3 17 18. Acts 10 44 45 1 Cor 12 4 5 6 2 Cor 3 7&punc; 8, 9. Rom. 1, 2.21&punc; 22 Psal. 147 19&punc; 20.</NOTE> all who are true and sincere Believers in the Lord Jesus Christ, as he dyed for us &amp; rose again, are under a peculiar and special Ministration of the Spirit, and have peculiar Illumi|nations and Revelations of God, and many peculiar and special Operations, Influences, Gifts, and Fruits of the Spirit, that none others have, how|ever just and conscientious they may be in their meer <HI>Gentile</HI> state under th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Law, and Ministration thereof, such as <HI>Co<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters">lius</HI> was before he received the Faith of Christ, by <HI>Peter</HI>'s Prea|ching.</P>
